Rhett Code of Law Challenge Hackathon
Team Cease & Desist
Problem statement 1
Execution Roadmap
Status: In Progress

Phase 1: Environment Initialization and Infrastructure
[x] Repository and Environment: Initialize the Git repository. Set up a Python 3.12 virtual environment and create the requirements file including streamlit, google-genai, requests, PyMuPDF, and python-dotenv

[x] API Validation: Generate and test the Gemini 2.5 Flash API key via the modern Google GenAI SDK. Generate and test the Sarvam API key via direct REST implementation

[x] UI Skeleton: Deploy the Streamlit application establishing a two-column layout for the file uploader, document preview, and analysis output

Phase 2: Document Extraction Pipeline
[x] PDF Extraction Integration: Implement PyMuPDF to accept PDF files and convert them into clean, structured text strings locally

[x] Text Normalization: Write utility functions to clean the extracted text, removing unnecessary whitespace or artifact characters before passing the data to the LLM

[x] Fallback Mechanism: Create a predefined, hardcoded text variable of a sample contract to guarantee uninterrupted development and demo safety if the uploaded file is corrupted

Phase 3: Core Legal Intelligence and JSON Enforcement
[ ] Prompt Engineering: Draft a comprehensive system prompt for Gemini 2.5 Flash. The prompt must explicitly instruct the model to evaluate the text against the specified Indian frameworks

[ ] Schema Enforcement: Instruct the LLM to output exclusively in a strict JSON format containing overall risk scores, severity levels, and suggested redlines

[ ] Testing Inference: Feed the extracted text from Phase 2 into the Gemini model. Iterate on the prompt until the JSON output is perfectly consistent and parsing it with Python does not throw errors

Phase 4: Visual Redlining and Document Manipulation
[ ] Coordinate Mapping: Utilize PyMuPDF to iterate through the text snippets provided by the JSON output. Use the search methods to find the exact X and Y coordinates on the original PDF pages

[ ] Annotation Application: Programmatically draw red strikethrough lines over the located coordinates

[ ] Text Insertion: Draw a distinct bounding box adjacent to the struck-through text and insert the suggested replacement string

[ ] File Compilation: Save the annotated document to a temporary memory buffer and expose it as a downloadable file within the Streamlit interface

Phase 5: Voice Explainer and Multi-lingual Support
[ ] Translation API: Route the legal explanations from the JSON output through the Sarvam Translate REST API to convert the English analysis into Hindi or other regional languages

[ ] Audio Generation: Pass the translated text to the Sarvam Text-to-Speech REST API to generate raw audio bytes

[ ] UI Integration: Embed Streamlit's audio component next to each flagged clause in the analysis column, allowing the user to play the explanation dynamically

Phase 6: Contingency Caching and Pitch Refinement
[ ] Static Asset Generation: Process specific dummy contracts through the fully working pipeline. Save the final JSON outputs, the generated audio files, and the redlined PDFs locally

[ ] Offline Mode: Map the offline mode toggle to bypass all API calls and instantly load the pre-processed static assets to guarantee a flawless demonstration regardless of internet connectivity

[ ] Pitch Preparation: Finalize the narrative focusing on the technical difficulty of coordinate-based redlining and the socio-economic impact on Tier-2 Indian cities